snippet.textDisplay:
Favorites
1. V - The Empire Strikes Back
2. III - Revenge Of The Sith
3. IV - A New Hope
4. VI - Return Of The Jedi
5. Rogue One
6. I - The Phantom Menace
7. VII - The Force Awakens
8. VIII - The Last Jedi
9. Solo
10. II - Attack Of The Clones

Yes, I have Revenge Of The Sith as my 2nd favorite over A New Hope which is arguably the 2nd best of the franchise. The space battles and lightsaber duels were more spectacular in Episode III. By far my favorite from the prequels. There's alot of plot holes in it and some awful acting from Hayden and Natalie, but I can accept the flaws for its entertainment value.

Attack Of The Clones is the worst SW movie ever made. The last 45 minutes of that film was absolute trash. Worse than The Phantom Menace and even Solo. Somebody should just bury that film. Such a shame because AOTC started off so promising. Then it became like Moonraker at the end.

I think the more underrated SW film is the lowest-rated one in Rotten Tomatoes and IMDb. The Phantom Menace is better AOTC and even The Force Awakens and The Last Jedi. It's really not as bad as people remembered it. It had Darth Maul and some of the most spectacular lightsaber duels we have ever seen for a Star Wars film. And I didn't mind the pod racing.

Rogue One looks to be by far and away my favorite SW in this Disney era. Thank you, Gareth Edwards. What really, really helped was inserting Darth Vader in it. He's the greatest SW character ever and no SW film feels the same without him. I actually didn't love Rogue One at first. I saw it like 5x and appreciated it more each time while I began disliking The Force Awakens the more I watched that one.

Knowing Grace's taste and reading so many harsh reviews for The Rise Of Skywalker, I expect the new one to be in my bottom two to three. Maybe not worse than AOTC but still bad. This could be Captain Marvel level for MCU. It's being compared to the last season of Game Of Thrones and Spider-Man 3 for goodness sakes!

I will always love you, Empire. You will always be my favorite.

snippet.textDisplay: While I usually agree with Grace on most reviews, I mostly disagree on this one. Was it great? No. Was it good? Yes! It wrapped up the Skywalker Saga as best it could, made sense of some things shown in TLJ, had some great action sequences, and some truly heart felt moments. What stopped it from being great is that there are moments of cheese in there that could have been done better, or were completely unnecessary (like the Knights of Ren reference Grace made in the review). Ultimately though, it was satisfying to see and experience the conclusion of something that has been a part of my whole life (I was born the year A New Hope came out).

snippet.textDisplay: Regardless of what happens, or what the conversation is about the movie and the story - I am committed to saying I liked it, and praising the special effects and the score. And I'll leave it at that. I'm not even impressed by big time special effects, and don't go to see movies based on that. But story and character-wise, I checked out of this trilogy in the first 15 minutes of TFA. But, I love John Williams scores, I love the space battles, and the sprawling planet-scapes. For all I care I could go watch 2 hours of nothing but Star Wars inspired scenes with no story or characters. And that's what I'm pretending to do for this movie.

snippet.textDisplay: I consider both the prequels and sequels to be steaming piles of shit. But the difference is that the prequel's shit, much like fertiliser, allowed for other things to grow out of it, like the excellent Clone Wars animated series and a slew of good games. It expanded the universe in a positive way, even if the execution was very poor. The sequel's shit, on the other hand, is so putrid, so acidic, so corrosive that nothing will grow out of it. It's done the opposite of fertilising; it's salted the earth so that nothing will ever grow there. There will be no positive legacy from the sequels. Disney wants these sequels to father more movies, but they've castrated themselves.
